  "_meta": {
    "schema_version": 1,
    "description": "ICAO type-designator (Doc 8643) -> category. Curated subset covering the ~95% most-common contacts. Unknown types fall back to category 'unknown' from app/services/categorize.py.",
    "categories": ["commercial", "military", "helicopter", "ga", "unknown"],
    "_notes": {
      "ga": "Includes general aviation AND business/corporate jets and turboprops (FAA Part 91/135). The line between scheduled-commercial and corporate is fuzzy by ADS-B alone; we choose the airframe-defined split: scheduled airline mainline + regional = commercial; everything else with fixed wings (small piston, biz-jets, light turboprops, ag aircraft, owner-flown) = ga.",
      "commercial": "Scheduled airline service airframes — 737/A320 mainline, widebodies, regional jets (E190, CRJ), regional turboprops in airline use (ATR, Dash 8). Excludes biz-jet variants of same airframe family (e.g. BBJ737 is rare enough we don't carve it out).",
      "military": "Combat, transport, refuelling, training, surveillance under military operation. We include trainers used by air forces (HAWK, T6) even though some civilian copies exist; live ADS-B `military` flag from the feed is an independent signal that overrides this table.",
      "helicopter": "All rotorcraft — civilian or military. ADS-B doesn't reliably distinguish HEMS vs corporate vs offshore vs military lift; flag at airframe level here."
    }
  },
